      "content": "thanks. the issue is that they're specifically looking for patterns in traditional banking ledger hops. if i just move to crypto, they'll see the fiat-to-crypto bridge and use that to tie the wallet back to me. they have access to things a regular bank doesn't—they can see the metadata of where the signal originates. what's the most effective way to break that link so they can't use my digital footprint to track my actual location or movements?",
